Description: Fragment of rim and neck of East Greek pottery column-krater; cream slip; interior glazed with added red and white bands; maeander band on top of rim, squares on edge; underside of rim and neck glazed; graffito on top of rim.
Curator's comments: Marked in pencil '1'. Possibly from same vessel as 1965,0930.718 & 719
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.997)
